Lac, love & a little bit of sparkle ✨💫
I’m a woman in corporate who loves closing deals and collecting stories — and this one came from Jaipur. 💼✈️💕

Whenever I take a break from the screen, I find myself in places like Maniharon Ka Raasta, wandering through old markets that smell like history and sound like home.

If you’re ever in Jaipur and skip this street full of handmade lac bangles, you’re missing out on a slice of tradition that’s still made by hand — with molten lac, gold foil, and decades of skill.

Picked mine in gulabi pink & sunset gold — because when in the Pink City… 💗🌇

📍Maniharon Ka Raasta, Johri Bazaar
💡Tip: Carry cash, go early, and ask for a custom fit on the spot!

My life has turned into a circus, and I'm the juggler! 🤡

As I travel to a client meeting in another city, my mind is racing with thoughts of sales pitches, content creation, and not getting lost. 🤣

It's funny how talking about the daily grind is both relatable and exhausting. And, because why not, I've decided to throw in a fitness routine, just in case a magazine wants me on their cover! Through it all, I'm reminded to count my blessings.✨🙏🏼
